    {
      "title": "<span id=\"#11926\" class=\"scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold flex items-center\"><h1 class=\"inline !mb-1 scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold\">grateful</h1><div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(adj.)</div></span>",
      "html": "<p>1550年代，“令人愉悦的”，也指“充满感激之情，愿意回报所受恩惠”，源自废弃的形容词 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">grate</span> “令人愉悦的”，源自拉丁语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">gratus</span> “令人愉悦的”（来自 PIE 词根 <a href=\"/cn/word/*gwere-\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of *gwere- \" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">*gwere-</a>（2）的后缀形式，“支持”）。[Weekley]“一种非常不寻常的形成方式”。这是英语中使用 <a href=\"/cn/word/-ful\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of -ful \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">-ful</a> 从形容词中制造形容词的一种罕见的、不规则的情况（我能找到的唯一另一个例子是 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">direful</span> “以某种可怕的东西为特征或充满某种可怕的东西”，1580年代）。相关词汇： <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">Gratefully</span>（1540年代）； <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">gratefulness</span>。</p><ins class=\"adsbygoogle relative inline-block transition-all inline-block h-[250px] w-[300px]\" data-ad-slot=\"4000736339\" data-adtest=\"off\" data-ad-format=\"auto\" data-full-width-responsive=\"true\"></ins><blockquote class=\"bq-origin\"><i class=\"foreign notranslate\">Grateful</i> often expresses the feeling and the readiness to manifest the feeling by acts, even a long time after the rendering of the favor; <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">thankful</i> refers rather to the immediate acknowledgment of the favor by words. [Century Dictionary]</blockquote><blockquote><i class=\"foreign notranslate\">Grateful</i> 通常表达感觉和愿意通过行动表达感觉，即使在恩惠得到之后很长一段时间； <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">thankful</i> 则更多地指通过言辞立即对恩惠表示感激。[世纪词典]</blockquote>"
    }
  ],
